-- Barclays, Credit Suisse, Deutsche Bank Credit Ratings Cut by S&P
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   H a r p e r
-- 2013-07-02T21:09:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-02/barclays-credit-suisse-deutsche-bank-credit-ratings-cut-by-s-p.html
Standard & Poor’s Rating Services cut
the long-term counterparty credit ratings on Barclays Bank Plc,
Credit Suisse AG, and  Deutsche Bank AG (DBK)  to A from A+, S&P said in
a statement today.  The rating company also affirmed its ratings on  UBS AG (UBSN)  and
said the ratings on the banks are stable.  “Barclays, Credit Suisse, Deutsche Bank, and UBS are among
the most exposed in Europe to a combination of regulatory
initiatives being undertaken globally on capital market-related
businesses,” the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
